content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide assembly instructions:

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of 8 distinct blocks
- It has multiple layers built around two vertical orange cylindrical pillars
- There's an orange triangular roof piece on top of one pillar
- Two yellow rectangular platforms
- One red arch/tunnel piece
- One blue cubic block
- Two orange cylindrical columns
- One orange triangular roof piece

Required blocks and their arrangement:
- Bottom layer: Two vertical orange cylinders (Block #11)
- Middle layer: Two yellow horizontal platforms (Block #8)
- Upper layer: One red arch piece (Block #1), one blue cube (Block #5)
- Top layer: One orange triangular roof piece (Block #14)

Assembly sequence:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 11 (left vertical orange cylinder)
    Step2: Move block with index 11 (right vertical orange cylinder)
    Step3: Move block with index 8 (left yellow platform)
    Step4: Move block with index 8 (right yellow platform)
    Step5: Move block with index 1 (red arch piece)
    Step6: Move block with index 5 (blue cube)
    Step7: Move block with index 14 (orange triangular roof)
}

The structure builds up from the ground with the support pillars, then adds the platforms, followed by the architectural elements on top, and finally the roof piece.
